  "text": "The experimental data obtained from the saturation binding experiments performed on immunoimmobilized ␣6␤2*, ␣4␤2*, or ␣3␤4* subtypes or membrane-bound ␣3␤2 subtype were analyzed by means of a nonlinear least-square procedure using the LIGAND program as described by [CITATION_1] . The calculated binding parameters were obtained by simultaneously fitting three independent experiments. The selection of the best fitting (i.e., one-site versus two-site model) and evaluation of the statistical significance of the parameters (i.e., comparison of the binding parameters of the two groups) were based on the F test for the \"extra sum of square\" principle. A value of p Ͻ 0.05 was considered statistically significant [CITATION_2] . The K i values of the toxins on Epi binding were determined by means of the LIGAND program using the data obtained from three independent experiments and compared by means of the F test as described above.",
